{
    "word": "Slaughter",
    "definitions": [
        "The act of killing.",
        "The extensive, violent, bloody, or wanton destruction of life; carnage.",
        "The act of killing cattle or other beasts for market.",
        "To visit with great destruction of life; to kill; to slay in battle.",
        "To butcher; to kill for the market, as beasts."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "On war and mutual slaughter bent.",
        "Your castle is surprised; your wife and babes Savagely slaughtered."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. slautir, slaughter, slaghter, Icel. sl slain flesh, modified by OE. slaught, slaht, slaughter, fr. AS. sleaht a stroke, blow; both from the root of E. slay. See Slay, v. t., and cf. Onslaught.]"
}